Bak Kut Teh (Pork Rib Soup)

8 c water
2 tbsp ground white pepper
1 tbsp ground black pepper
2 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp salt
3 whole star anise
1 tsp cinnamon
20 garlic cloves
6 tsp dark shoyu
2 lbs pork ribs, rinsed and drained, cut into 4 pieces
cooked rice for serving

In a large pot, add all the ingredients, except the ribs, and bring to a boil over high heat. Add the ribs to the brothand bring back to a boil, then lower the heat and let it simmer on low for 1 hr and 15 min, or until the pork is tender. Turn off heat and cover for 10 min. Serve hot with rice.
